Russian Movers: Baltika, Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel, Rosneft

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-17T15:39:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/russian-equity-movers-baltika-rosneft-sberbank-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced
for the second day this week, rising 1.9 percent to 1,509.19 by
the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
rallied 1.9 percent to 1,663.86.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Baltika (PKBA RX), a beer producer controlled by
Carlsberg A/S, slipped the most in more than a week after its
parent slashed profit forecasts due to faltering sales in
Russia. The shares dropped 4.3 percent to 1,123 rubles, the
biggest loss since Aug. 8.  OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel (MAGN RX) jumped the most in
more than two months, adding 5.7 percent to 18.954 rubles. All
metals listed on the London Metal Exchange climbed, led by
copper, tin and nickel.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia â€™s largest oil producer, rose
for the second day this week, adding 2.4 percent to 211.31
rubles. Crude jumped to a two-week high in  New York , rising as
much as 2.7 percent to $89 a barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
